confconsole (0.9.4) precise; urgency=low

  * leverage debian networking tools (ifup/ifdown)

  * removed udhcpc dependency and demoted resolvconf to recommends

  * handle exceptions in a user friendly way (fault tolerant)

  * retain iface options which are already defined when updating interfaces configuration

  * added support for multiple nameservers

  * moved template to /etc/confconsole/usage.txt and set as conffile

  * template changes

  * bugfixes

  * misc

 -- Alon Swartz <alon@sterilesecurity.com>  Wed, 30 Sep 2009 19:06:36 +0200

confconsole (0.9.3) precise; urgency=low

  * new configuration variable: CONFCONSOLE_FGVT

  * handle use cases as expected (user experience)

  * updated default button labels to make more sense

  * fixed static nameserver configuration to persist across reboots

  * intercept exit signal and verify whether to quit (ESC, ALT+?)

  * validate all input prior to attempting to apply them

  * template changes

 -- Alon Swartz <alon@sterilesecurity.com>  Thu, 29 Jan 2009 13:42:43 +0200

